    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>14 Oct 1858</date>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Having written to you<lb/> heretofore I consider it proper to<lb/>
                keep you posted in the <persName>Wise</persName> matters.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As I told you he issued an<lb/> extra political sheet on
                    <date>Monday</date><lb/> filled with the most absurd nonsense,<lb/> and
                blackguardism. Abusing me &amp;<lb/> all others who differed with him,<lb/>
                inserting however this “If he (<add>?</add>)<lb/> “will get one respectable man
                to<lb/> “sign his (my) card we will take<lb/> “back every word we said” Where<lb/>
                upon I procured the signature of<lb/> seven respectable men adopting<lb/> my card,
                sent the same to him &amp;<lb/> told him he must either pronounce<lb/> those me not
                respectable or retract</p>
            <p rend="The following is written at the top of the page.">20-402</p>
            <p rend=" The following is written in pencil near the top right of the page.">Saint
                    <persName>Isaac<lb/> Mayer Wise</persName><lb/>
                <add>?</add></p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>all he has said of me. He replies<lb/> winces &amp; <sic>prevarecates</sic> &amp;
                asks me to<lb/> point out the portions of his paper<lb/> which give
                    <sic>offence</sic> &amp; he will do so<lb/> as to mine &amp; three arbitrators
                shall<lb/> determine what shall be done by<lb/> either. I demand his retraction<lb/>
                he again does not comply but fi<lb/>=nally consents to leave the whole mat<lb/>ter
                to three persons which I have <add>a</add>greed<lb/> to do. If it had not been for
                public<lb/> scandal a cowhide would have been<lb/> his merited chastisement, as it
                is he<lb/> has lost caste amongst friend &amp; foe,<lb/> all alike utterly
                denouncing his<lb/> course. He has acted in a most<lb/> vile &amp; despicable
                manner, first<lb/> in taking a bribe to support any<lb/> political party, secondly
                in attemp<lb/><sic>x</sic>ting to carry out his views of poli<lb/>=tics in a
                religious paper, thirdly<lb/> his views were antagonist to ¾ of<lb/> his
                subscribers, fourthly his</p>
            <pb n="3R"/>
            <p>scandalous abuse of men so eminently<lb/> his superior, in every point of view<lb/>
                moral, religious, intellectual or in<lb/> any other way. Without<lb/> knowing what
                if any political pre<lb/>ferences you may have, you must<lb/> rejoice in the defeat
                &amp; total route<lb/> of him &amp; his party. He has gone<lb/> today to
                    <placeName>Louisville</placeName> will return on<lb/>
                <date>Tuesday</date> &amp; then will have to appear<lb/> before the three who I
                choose &amp; defend<lb/> himself against me. You can<lb/> have no idea of the
                universal con<lb/>demnation he meets here among<lb/> all classes jews &amp;
                christians.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Did you receive his extras called<lb/> “Observers”. If you wish to
                know<lb/> more address yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Abraham</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
